description: Describes the specified key pairs or all of your key pairs. For more information about key pairs, see Amazon EC2 key pairs in the Amazon EC2 User Guide.

parameters.name: KeyNames
parameters.description: The key pair names. Default: Describes all of your key pairs. (string) ---

parameters.name: KeyPairIds
parameters.description: The IDs of the key pairs. (string) ---

parameters.name: IncludePublicKey
parameters.description: If true, the public key material is included in the response. Default: false.

parameters.name: Filters
parameters.description: The filters. key-pair-id - The ID of the key pair. fingerprint - The fingerprint of the key pair. key-name - The name of the key pair. tag-key - The key of a tag assigned to the resource. Use this filter to find all resources assigned a tag with a specific key, regardless of the tag value. tag:<key> - The key/value combination of a tag assigned to the resource. Use the tag key in the filter name and the tag value as the filter value. For example, to find all resources that have a tag with the key Owner and the value TeamA, specify tag:Owner for the filter name and TeamA for the filter value. (dict) --- A filter name and value pair that is used to return a more specific list of results from a describe operation. Filters can be used to match a set of resources by specific criteria, such as tags, attributes, or IDs. If you specify multiple filters, the filters are joined with an AND, and the request returns only results that match all of the specified filters. For more information, see List and filter using the CLI and API in the Amazon EC2 User Guide. Name (string) --- The name of the filter. Filter names are case-sensitive. Values (list) --- The filter values. Filter values are case-sensitive. If you specify multiple values for a filter, the values are joined with an OR, and the request returns all results that match any of the specified values. (string) ---

nested_items.name: KeyPairId
nested_items.description: The ID of the key pair.

nested_items.name: Tags
nested_items.description: Any tags applied to the key pair.

nested_items.name: CreateTime
nested_items.description: If you used Amazon EC2 to create the key pair, this is the date and time when the key was created, in ISO 8601 date-time format, in the UTC time zone.

nested_items.name: KeyName
nested_items.description: The name of the key pair.

nested_items.name: KeyFingerprint
nested_items.description: If you used  CreateKeyPair to create the key pair:
For RSA key pairs, the key fingerprint is the SHA-1 digest of the DER encoded private key.
For ED25519 key pairs, the key fingerprint is the base64-encoded SHA-256 digest, which is the default for OpenSSH, starting with OpenSSH 6.8.
